column2: Partly cloudy.  Checked it with sun out.
First time I've noticed slight algae.  Very calm water-have had several days of bright sun.
Water very clear.  No algae blooms apparent today-temperature about 65 degrees.  Beautiful day- slight breeze.
Clear- sunny- 65 degrees- slight breeze- slight algae bloom.
Clear and sunny- 55 degrees- slight breeze- just had a week of rain and heavy winds.  Turned lake over for sure.  Water appears clean and clear.
Water appears clear-but possible some sediment due to lake turnover.
Had heavy wave action earlier in the week.
Water lily's starting to show leafs- cabbage weeds very late in growing - just started.
Partly cloudy and 60 degrees.  Loon sited 4/10.
Hazy wind at 6 mph 70 degrees. trees leafed out.
Slight overcast. a chop on water. 75 F. had 6 1/2" rain past 3 weeks. water more brown. swamp drainage. tannin.
Clear. 80 F. choppy. 2" of rain 3 or 4 days ago.
Hazy. 78 F. calm. 3" of rain 2 days ago. lake rose over 1'.
Clear. 78 F. calm. water color more brown than 1998. more rain this year.
Clear. 65 F. calm. water color darker brown. rain during week.
Clear- calm- 75 degrees.  Too many large high powered boats for a small lake the last 3 years.
Partly cloudy- calm- 70 degrees.  Had heavy rain 12 days ago.  Lake level very high- water browner.
Partly cloudy- windy- 78 degrees.  Browner water this year.
Sunny- slight haze- 47 degrees.  10 inches of snow 10/7.
Hazy- with sun shining through - 1st time in 4 days.  60 degrees- chop on water.
Hazy- breezy- and the temperature is 70 degrees.
Mostly sunny- breezy- and the temperature is 80 degrees.
Mostly sunny- slight breeze- and the temperature is 70 degrees.
Sunny- breezy- the temperature is 70 degrees- and no one else on the water.
Sunny- some breeze- and the temperature is 82 degrees.
Sunny- breezy- and the temperature is 90 degrees.
Partly cloudy- some breeze- and the temperature is 80 degrees.
Cloudy- west wind- and the temperature is 60 degrees.
Hazy but sunny- windy- and the temperature is 60 degrees.
Sunny- calm- and the temperature is 60 degrees.
Clear and sunny- calm- the temperature is 70 degrees- 1/2" or rain on 6/4.
Hazy- calm- and the temperature is 80 degrees.
Clear and sunny.  The temperature is 74 degrees.
Partly cloudy- calm- and the temperature is 78 degrees.
Clear- gusty wind- and the temperature is 72 degrees.
Sunny but hazy- slight breeze- and the temperature is 70 degrees.
Sunny- choppy- temperature is 58 degrees- 5.5" or rain over past 10 days.
60 F- clear and sunny- east wind.
60 F- Cloudy- NW wind- choppy water.
80 F- scattered clouds- small chop on water.
80 F- almost calm- sunny with broken clouds.
64 F- windy- sunny with broken clouds.
60 F- windy- sunny with heavy broken clouds.
cloudy- cool- breezy.  1 loon- 2 osprey- 1 eagle- 2 geese noticed. cloudy- breezy- cool.
Saw pair of loons today.  Sunny- breezy.
pair of loons- 1 adult and 1 immature bald eagle seen today.
Saw pair of loons- color turning grey-brown.
1 bald eagle.  No loons heard or seen this weekend.
very windy- unable to test temp accurately to bottom due to drifting
calm- 70 degrees- sunny. pair of loons seen on lake- 1 osprey- 1 eagle
Very windy - unsure if temps are accurate or we were drifting too much.
Very calm- sunny. 1 eagle- pair of loons. Water clear- but  pollen floating on surface over large areas.
too windy- drifting too much to let thermometer sink to approp level.  Only tested to 9 ft.
Very calm- sunny and warm. Pair of loons- 1 osprey.
cloudy + calm. pair of loons seen
pair of loons. breezy- partly sunny

cloudy- drizzle- not windy.  Took chlorophyll and phosphorus samples- but had no sulfuric acid left from last year to set phophorus sample.  Loons calling on the lake.  Saw 3 snapping turtles laying eggs along the roadside.
no wind - lake surface like glass.
1 loon - changing color to grey.  Very windy - unable to get accurate temps at lower levels.
Water level very high.  Memorial weekend and few have docks in.  Pair of loons seen on lake.  Patches of ice still on lake 2 wks ago- but now no ice.
Overcast and very slight breeze.  Have not seen or heard loons on the lake for past month.
noticed clumps of algae along windward shore.
2 loons- no young seen. lake calm.
